Date:10/15/2007 11:55:49 AM
From:Jurgis Bekepuris
The problem is that economists will claim that oil is cyclical and WILL go down
from here. Peak oilers will claim that "this time is different" and oil WILL
NOT go down and rather will go up parabolically. If economists are right, it
does not matter that "at the current price of oil, many, if not most, energy
stocks look like good values". This is always true at the top of the cycle:
companies look cheap, since market expects the earnings to drop drastically on
the down cycle.

Bill Miller, for example, is in the economist camp so far, but he is wavering.
He said something like if oil drops by the end of the year, economists are
right, if it hits new peak, then this time is different. :)

Buffett - who knows - but apparently he sold Petro China - but then Petro China
is hugely expensive now, much more than domestic majors.
