By Ben White in New York and Jeremy Grant in Washington
Wednesday Oct 17 2007 19:20

The Securities and Exchange Commission is investigating stock sales by Angelo
Mozilo, chief executive of Countrywide Financial (NYSE:CFC) , the largest US
mortgage lender hit by the subprime mortgage crisis.

The probe into Mr Mozilo is part of a broader look by the SEC at stock sales
made by executives at mortgage lenders caught up in the subprime crisis,
according to a person familiar with the &#173;matter.

Countrywide spokesman Rick Simon said: "As a matter of policy, Countrywide does
